' plan-59-D Phase 4: a resource is closed on EVERY exit path where it did NOT
' escape. plan-59-D adds a scope-exit skip for an *escaping* resource; this
' fixture pins that the skip is inert everywhere else — which is the failure mode
' that leaks silently rather than the one that crashes.
'
' §15 lists the exit paths. Four had no resource fixture before this one: EXIT
' (loop), CONTINUE, an auto-propagated failure, and TRAP routing. The others are
' covered by the sibling control-flow-resource-* fixtures (normal, RETURN, FAIL,
' PROPAGATE).
'
' The assertion is FILE DESCRIPTOR EXHAUSTION, not exit code. Each helper opens a
' file and leaves by one path without returning it, 2000 times over. If the
' scope-exit cleanup were skipped on any of these paths the descriptors would
' accumulate and the run would fail long before the end — macOS's default soft
' limit is 256, so a leak on any single path is caught within the first handful of
' iterations. A leak is invisible to exit status, which is exactly why it has to
' be provoked like this rather than asserted directly.
IMPORT fs
IMPORT io

' EXIT: the resource is live in the loop body when EXIT leaves the loop.
FUNC leaveByExit(path AS String) AS Nothing
  MUT n AS Integer = 0
  WHILE n < 4
    RES f AS File = fs::openFile(path)
    EXIT WHILE
  WEND
  RETURN NOTHING
END FUNC

' CONTINUE: the resource is live where CONTINUE jumps to the next iteration, so
' every one of the 4 iterations must close its own handle.
FUNC leaveByContinue(path AS String) AS Nothing
  MUT n AS Integer = 0
  WHILE n < 4
    RES f AS File = fs::openFile(path)
    n = n + 1
    CONTINUE WHILE
  WEND
  RETURN NOTHING
END FUNC

' Auto-propagated failure: opening a nonexistent path fails and the failure
' leaves this function with no explicit FAIL. The resource opened before it has
' NOT escaped and must still be closed (§15.6: "On an error exit before the
' return, the resources are still closed by the function's scope").
FUNC leaveByAutoPropagate(path AS String) AS Nothing
  RES f AS File = fs::openFile(path)
  RES bad AS File = fs::openFile("/nonexistent-p59d/missing.txt")
  RETURN NOTHING
END FUNC

' TRAP routing: the same failure, routed to this function's own handler, which
' then returns normally. The resource is live when the route happens.
FUNC leaveByTrapRoute(path AS String) AS Nothing
  RES f AS File = fs::openFile(path)
  RES bad AS File = fs::openFile("/nonexistent-p59d/missing.txt")
  RETURN NOTHING
  TRAP(e)
    RETURN NOTHING
  END TRAP
END FUNC

FUNC main AS Integer
  LET path AS String = "tests/rt-behavior/resources/resource-exit-path-cleanup-rt/src/main.mfb"
  MUT i AS Integer = 0
  WHILE i < 2000
    leaveByExit(path)
    leaveByContinue(path)
    leaveByTrapRoute(path)
    leaveByAutoPropagate(path) TRAP(e)
      RECOVER
    END TRAP
    i = i + 1
  WEND
  io::print("exit-paths=" & toString(i))
  io::print("done")
  RETURN 0
END FUNC
